The paper proposes a model that integrates knowledge graph embeddings and pre-trained language representations for various NLP tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques and algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with information retrieval and knowledge graphs, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases).
